# File encoding is load-bearing in this project - see the rules in HANDOVER.md.
# The .ps1 files must stay pure ASCII, because PowerShell 5.1 reads a .ps1 with
# no BOM as ANSI; the .json, .md and .html files must keep their UTF-8 BOM, so
# Notepad on an older server renders the Thai correctly.
#
# Pinning the line ending here keeps a clone made on Linux, WSL or a machine
# with a different core.autocrlf from handing PowerShell a file that differs
# from the one that was tested. Git only ever rewrites line endings and never
# touches the BOM, so both rules above survive the round trip either way.
* text=auto eol=crlf
